<br>
You didn't tell me anything I don't know, and I'm not sure where your example is going.  Nothing you wrote seemed to respond to my post.<br>
<br>
Summary of my point:<br>
<br>
Evade nerf is obviously intended to reduce rogue damage output (if it was only about us &quot;dropping off&quot; the list, the change would not have needed to be as severe).<br>
<br>
This is accomplished by either:<br>
<br>
1) A reduction in backstabs due to rogues tanking more (and therefore facing the wrong side of the mob).  This will happen to rogues who continue their current tactic of pushing the BS button every time it refreshes (pretty much all rogues).  They will be constantly at #1-#2 on the hate list, and a failed evade will mean a lost BS attempt while you tank another round.<br>
<br>
or,<br>
<br>
2) Forcing the rogue to change tactics, and withhold Backstabs at the beginning of the fight while they pre-emptively evade.  Then using Backstabs in moderation.<br>
<br>
Net result is lower damage, no matter how you look at it.<br>
<br>
And then there's the uber mob multi-group dilemma.  Multiple rogues will have even a harder time of getting their backstabs in, because either they will be holding back from BS'ing, or else they will be alternating with each other on the top of the hate list until all but one or two are dead.<br>
<br>
Back to what you wrote, not really sure I understand your point.  Sure, the people attacking the front of a mob lose a small bit of damage due to ripostes and dodges...but what does that have to do with rogue damage? (Other than when the rogue is tanking, which will obviously reduce rogue damage output even more.)<br>
<br>
When I'm limited to frontal attacks, I'll do a little over 1k damage/minute.  If I can backstab, I do over 4k damage/minute.<br>
<br>
Note this is post-55 with double backstab.<br>
<br>
Again, the fallout from this nerf will be that rogues will no longer be able to press that BS button every time it refreshes with near-impunity.  Rogues will have to be more conscious of their damage output, and resist the temptation to click that button every 5 seconds or deal with the wrong end of the mob.  If you are in a single group and can time your evades off a primary tank, it's not really an issue.  But in a multi-group high level raid it's a serious concern.<br>
<br>
Net result is less damage any way you slice it.<br>
<br>
Guessing somewhere in the range of a 40% damage reduction, based on my own combat style.<br>
<br>
<br>
I had a preview of this change last night in Sirens Grotto fighting underwater.  Evade was next to impossible (maybe once a fight if I got really luck) as I was constantly swimming to get to the back of the mob when I got a respite from tanking.  I'd only get maybe 3-4 backstabs in each battle.  And I took more damage in the underwater fights than any other time during the night.  With limited evade and only a couple backstabs I spent a heck of a lot of time tanking.  I cringe every time the BS button is up and I can't press it, but we're gonna have to get used to that.<br>
<br>
On the plus side I picked up a new 20 AC cloak to replace my HBC.  With the changes to work as I expect, I'll need the AC.  A week ago I wouldn't have even considered that replacement.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/urohaise.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rohaise</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/9/01 12:58:38 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Zen and the Art of Auto Mechanics</span><hr size=1> I like Pharius's personal pic:<br>
