<IMG SRC=http://www.geocities.com/txsurfer1/backstab2.gif><br>
<br>
That's exactly what rogues do now.  Click click click click click every time it refreshes.<br>
<br>
That's the problem that Verant is addressing with the nerf.  By forcing us to keep that button un-grayed longer it means rogue damage is contained.<br>
<br>
And a side effect will be as TibisHatter said, diminishing returns for the more rogues you have on raids.  Once you have maybe 2 rogues, you're just as well off having a ranger in that spot.  Which is good for class diversity.<br>
<br>
I'm the person in my guild who determines fight order, and group composition on raids.  This is going to affect the job I do greatly.  More than 2 rogues means the 3rd+ will be waiting in a support group until one of the first rogues die before they will be allowed to move in.  Rangers and lower level monks will take the place of the 3rd+ rogues in the primary groups.<br>
