Evade had been well covered here and I am pleased to see that kendrik has started some real testing.<br>
<br>
<br>
I would like to broach a couple other things in the hopes that kendrik is reading, and to get some opinions. They are small tweaks that make sense and are not a problem to implement.<br>
<br>
*The Sense Trap Skill needs to be looked at. With the implementation of new traps in velious this skill has become something in the rogue arsenal that can really be put to use. The problem is that the &quot;sensing&quot; radius of the sense traps skill is tiny. This coupled with the fast the the recycle time of about 5 or 6 seconds makes this skill almost worthless..better to spring the trap and deal with it rather spend 20 minutes in a tiny area trying to sense a trap. <br>
<br>
--The Fix: Increase the sense trap radius by a good amount and drastically lower the recycle time . Sense Traps is a skill that you should be able to use on the fly while dungeon crawling, not sense, wait 5secs, take a step, sense, wait 5 sec, etc etc.. I would like to see this as something that I can click constantly in a strange dungeon, if something turns up I can yell stop and proceed to disarm without having to seriously slow down my group.<br>
<br>
*Poison resist: Being masters of poisoning and poisons you would naturally think that our poison resist would gain in  power as we gained in level. Somebody that handles poisonious snakes all their life stands a much better chance of surviving the poison than somebody who does not. <br>
<br>
--The Fix: give us 1pt of poison resist a level. warriors get magic resist, give us poison. not much to ask<br>
